<b>Posted On:</b> 1:38 p.m. 22/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Hope this can help<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/rallos_zek.cgi?read=11" TARGET=_self>Hope this can help</A> (Schrocken)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> Have had some people take loot from

<BR>&gt; my body, but who can resist that :)
<P>This problem will actually "go away". A little anyway.
<P>When I was low level (1-5) and I saw a dead body, I looted it for the coins. Most of the time, there wasn't any items worth taking. I mean, two snake fangs, a couple of bone shards, that sort of thing. It would have taken longer for me to sell them than it was worth.
<P>As I got higher in levels, I stopped looting so much. One, because I knew how much it sucked for the loot-ee, and, two, because most people didn't carry that much "good" loot. Looting for a few silver didn't make sense when you could be fingered as the looter. You can't /con a dead body. That guy you just looted for 5 silver might turn out to be a 15th level Warrior who holds a grudge against looters.
<P>Of course, the cycle repeats as you break into new zones. Once I graduated into the next harder zone, it was like being a newbie again, and I started looting....
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
